quran[18]{c,v,t}:
  10,53,"They will desire thee to inform them whether this be true? SAY: Yes! by my Lord it is the truth: and it is not ye who can weaken Him"
  10,54,"And every soul that hath sinned, if it possessed all that is on earth, would assuredly ransom itself therewith; and they will proclaim their repentance when they have seen the punishment: and there shall be a rightful decision between them, and they shall not be unjustly dealt with"
  10,55,Is not whatever is in the Heavens and the Earth God's? Is not then the promise of God true? Yet most of them know it not
  10,56,"He maketh alive and He causeth to die, and to Him shall ye return"
  10,57,"O men! now hath a warning come to you from your Lord, and a medicine for what is in your breasts, and a guidance and a mercy to believers"
  10,58,"SAY: Through the grace of God and his mercy! and in this therefore let them rejoice: better is this than all ye amass"
  10,59,"SAY: What think ye? of what God hath sent down to you for food, have ye made unlawful and lawful? SAY: Hath God permitted you? or invent ye on the part of God"
  10,60,But what on the day of Resurrection will be the thought of those who invent a lie on the part of God? Truly God is full of bounties to man; but most of them give not thanks
  10,61,"Thou shalt not be employed in affairs, nor shalt thou read a text out of the Koran, nor shall ye work any work, but we will be witnesses over you when ye are engaged therein: and not the weight of an atom on Earth or in Heaven escapeth thy Lord; nor is there aught that is less than this or greater, but it is in the perspicuous Book"
  10,62,"Are not the friends of God, those on whom no fear shall come, nor shall they be put to grief"
  10,63,They who believe and fear God
  10,64,"For them are good tidings in this life, and in the next! There is no change in the words of God! This, the great felicity"
  10,65,"And let not their discourse grieve thee: for all might is God's: the Hearer, the Knower, He"
  10,66,"Is not whoever is in the Heavens and the Earth subject to God? What then do they follow who, beside God, call upon deities they have joined with Him? They follow but a conceit, and they are but liars"
  10,67,"It is He who hath ordained for you the night wherein to rest, and the lightsome day. Verily in this are signs for those who hearken"
  10,68,"They say, \"God hath begotten children.\" No! by his glory! He is the self-sufficient. All that is in the Heavens and all that is in the Earth is His! Have ye warranty for that assertion? What! speak ye of God that which ye know not"
  10,69,"SAY: Verily, they who devise this lie concerning God shall fare ill"
  10,70,"A portion have they in this world! Then to us they return! Then make we them to taste the vehement torment, for that they were unbelievers"